{
  "stem": "1400.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Good old Oregon rain.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This year.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was constant and always around that-- around us, the beating.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you don't-- didn't push the wagon or didn't do-- or didn't run fast enough, they-- whenever they ordered us to go into the-- to the bed or the-- if they caught us on the way-- or they just, on a whim, the kapos were brutal.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They, they, they-- some-- I saw some people's arm broken with a stick.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I-- the only thing I-- like a little-- I don't know how should I explain it-- I just would try to hide from them and get in the middle of the group so I don't be on the edge where they-- where they-- and I tried to do the work, because that was the only thing, or, or the thing what they told me to do to get away.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But even then, I didn't, didn't always got away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But luckily I wasn't injured behind-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] able to recover from it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And many nights, when-- even though it was said you can't leave the barrack, I saw people hanging on the barbed wire, electrified in the morning.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We heard their scream when they grab the wire at night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Walked out and just grabbed the wire and-- they couldn't take it anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't know what made me going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I didn't grasp the intensity of the situation or I just-- like a little animal, I was try to do-- I make another day.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I, I-- in that 10 months in concentration camp, I saw more dead people that I can count, and I, I, I have probably-- never will see in my life, I hope.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The cleanings?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Auschwitz, it was fair.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I say fair.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
